[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mSO YOU WANT TO BE A SYSOP? by Wally Byczek                                   [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41m                              WallyWorld BBS 1989                            [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mTo start a BBS, you first need a computer. No matter what computer you       [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mcurrently have, it won't be large enough or powerful enough for what you     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mintend to do. And since you can't take the board down (unless you run a      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mkiddy board that bounces up and down or runs only between the time           [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mschool lets out and Daddy comes home) to do your own work, you will need     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41manother computer that you can ill afford. Next you have to find a BBS        [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41msoftware package. This can take months, or you can write your own if you     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mare so inclined. This can take years. Next, unless you are starting a        [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mkiddy board, you will need a phone line other than the one that you          [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mnormally converse on. Depending on the Telco's mood, personnel, and the      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mimminence of a strike, this could be done in as little as 2 weeks or it      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mmay never happen. Next, if you plan to run doors on your board, you must     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mnow spend long distance dollars in scouring other boards for evaluation and  [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41maquisition of these games. Naturally, your external file protocols don't     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mcome with your BBS software, so you have to again scour the countryside to   [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mfind them. Utilities for your BBS are also an after thought and have to      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mbe obtained in a similar fashion. All of these external programs have to     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mbe registered after a while, since most stop working after a while or have   [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41man annoying feature about them until they are registered. All of the above   [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mitems take money! and plenty of it!                                          [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41m                                                                             [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mWhile we are on the subject of money, you must obtain a modem. Whatever      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mmodem you currently have will not be supported by the BBS software. This     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mis some sort of unwritten law pertaining to writing communication software.  [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mBe prepared to open your wallet wide. No, your old Hayes 300 won't be good   [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41menough. People even hate 1200 baud these days, and the teenagers seem to     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mhave USR HST's these days and will complain vociferously if they can't       [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41maccess you at 14.4.                                                          [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41m                                                                             [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mNow you pick a name for your BBS. Whatever you choose will be                [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mridiculed by 20% of those who see it. Another 50% will offer suggestions     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mthat are worse than the one you chose. The remaining 30% won't care.         [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41m                                                                             [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mNext comes the wonderful task of installing your board. You have your        [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mmachine. If you just bought it, that means formatting your hard disk,        [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41minstalling DOS, and ASNI drivers and Lord knows what else that you need      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mfor your board. If you already have the machine, you may as well go ahead    [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mand reformat it anyway. Something will guarantee that you will have to       [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mdo this before you are done.                                                 [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mThe manual for the BBS software was most likely written                      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mby the author's 10 year old and was mimeographed. It got wet in the mail     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mand smeared as well, so at least 30% of the manual will be physically        [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41museless. The rest is just procedurally useless.                              [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41m                                                                             [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mNext comes the fun task of deciding on your board structure. Who can do      [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mwhat and when can they do it. You must design your menus and opening screens.[1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mYou have to get a pretty good stock of files, because no one will upload to  [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41myou unless you have something there for them to take first. (not that it     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mmatters, I suppose, since even if you DO have files, they won't upload       [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mmuch anyway.)                                                                [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41m                                                                             [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mNext comes the security aspect. You can leave your board wide open so that   [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41musers with the name of Benny Beanfart, Dr. Rape, Crack, Hack, File Attack,   [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mDR DEATH, etc can come in and do anything they like. Or, you can lock it     [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mup so tight that no one will call. There is no compromise on this.           [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41m                                                                             [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mNext you must build events or prepare to live at your keyboard. A BBS HAS    [1m[34;41m∫[40m
[1m[34;41m∫[1m[37;41mto be backed up. If you can't afford a high density backup medium such as    [1m[34;41m∫[40m
